by having the lateral keel odontodes almost perpendicular to the plates (
<emphasis box="[1361,1391,1601,1624]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">vs.</emphasis>
sloped posteriorly) and by having the longest keel odontodes longer than the plates in the lateral-line row in the adult. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Armbruster &amp; Page" authorityYear="2006" box="[831,1100,1696,1720]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pterygoplichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="406" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="weberi">
<emphasis box="[831,1100,1696,1720]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">Pterygoplichthys weberi</emphasis>
