<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pterygoplichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="406" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">P. punctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the buccal papilla partially divided in the adult (
<emphasis box="[939,969,1761,1784]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">vs.</emphasis>
fully divided at all ages; 
<figureCitation box="[1238,1298,1761,1784]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[831,870,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[831,1474,653,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-567@1.[831,1474,653,1797]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Mouth and buccal papilla (indicated by arrow) of a. Pterygoplichthys punctatus, MCP 35755, 203.1 mm SL, b. P. weberi, FMNH 96959, holotype, 183.9 mm SL, c. P. multiradiatus, AUM 18947, 153.3 mm SL. Photos by J.W. Armbruster and L.M. Page." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4566984" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4566984/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="406">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
